Hi @whatisAI, thanks for reporting the issue, yes this is limited by the default lightgbm runner implementation, which doesn't allow users to easily pass through additional parameters to `predict` method.

An easy workaround is to use BentoML's custom runner interface, see this example here: https://docs.bentoml.org/en/latest/concepts/runner.html#custom-model-runner

You could do something like this:

```python
bento_model = bentoml.lightgbm.get("my_model:latest")

class MyLightGBMRunner(bentoml.Runnable):
    SUPPORTED_RESOURCES = ("cpu",)
    SUPPORTS_CPU_MULTI_THREADING = True

    def __init__(self):
        self.model = bentoml.lightbm.load_model(bento_model)

    @bentoml.Runnable.method(batchable=False)
    def predict(self, input_data):
        return self.model.predict(input_data, predict_contrib=True)

model_runner = bentoml.Runner(MyLightGBMRunner, models=[bento_model])

```

